post_text:
NOTICE OF PUBLIC MEETING

On June 10, 2020 at 11:00 a.m. a meeting conducted by Dunlap CUSD #323 will take place virtually on Zoom. The purpose of the meeting will be to discuss the district’s plans for providing special education services to students with disabilities who attend private schools and homeschool within the district for the 2020-2021 school year. If you are a parent of a home-schooled student who has been, or may be identified with a disability, and you reside within the boundaries of Dunlap CUSD #323, you are urged to attend. If you have further questions pertaining to this meeting, please contact Alyssa Hart at (309)691-3955.

Once again we are need of more donations to help feed students in need during the evening and weekends.
Plus hygiene bags for families in need.

If interested in donating please drop off in front of DHS from 11:30am- 1:30pm on Sunday 4/19/20.
There will be a tub labeled donations.
One person at a time to respect social distancing.

We need:
tuna/meat in cans or individual packets
Mac n cheese
Ramon noodles
Soup
Canned vegetables
Individual milk (not refrigerated)

Shampoo/conditioner
Deodorant for men and women
Individual toothbrushes
lotion

Thank you,
Alyssa Hart
ahart@dunlapcusd.net

shared_text:

February 28 at 9:26 AM ·

Congratulations to Mandy Ellis, the Illinois Principals Association's Elementary Principal of the Year!!!!!!

Mandy is the principal of Dunlap Grade School, part of Dunlap School District #323. She is a great leader and is well respected by her peers. We are honored to be a part of her award ceremony and celebration.

post_text:
School Board Members Day

November 15 will mark the official statewide observance of School Board Members Day in Illinois. This honorary day is an opportunity for the district and community to show support for the Board of Education and their commitment to providing a local voice for your educational vision.

School board members serve the public as unpaid volunteers for the benefit of the students and community residents. They dedicate a significant amount of their own personal time to the district, something that is often overlooked. They attend numerous extracurricular events and work long hours to ensure students have access to the educational resources they need to succeed. This dedication often takes them away from time that could be spent with their own family.

Successful communities have high quality public schools which equates to a thriving local economy and a destination community for families. A great school system is a source of
local pride among residents.

Please take a moment to thank our local school board members on this honorary day.

#ThankABoardMember

Dunlap School District is excited to share a heartfelt Congratulations to DGS Principal Mandy Ellis and HGES Assistant Principal Michaela Rychener!

Mrs. Ellis has been named Elementary Principal of the Year, and Mrs. Rychener has been named Elementary Assistant Principal of the Year by the Illinois Principals' Association Central Illinois Valley Region!

This is a wonderful honor for Mrs. Ellis and Mrs. Rychener to be acknowledged for the dedication and passion they bring to the students, families, and staff each day. Please join us in congratulating them!

post_text:
The week of August 5-10, Dunlap Library patrons can have fines up to $5 forgiven in exchange for a donation of school supplies. The donated supplies will benefit Dunlap Gives Back, a program run by the Dunlap School District to benefit teachers and families in need.

The guidelines:
- Up to $5.00 in LATE fines, on DPLD items ONLY, per card forgiven
- Does not apply to processing fees, lost item charges, or late fines on other libraries items.
- Must be done at the circulation desk, no emails or phone calls
- Donated items can be placed in a box near the circulation desk.

Items you can donate:
- Dunlap Gives Back will accept non-perishable breakfast items, gift cards, backpacks, pencils, paper, folders, markers, and crayons.

Please ask Amy any questions:

Amy Edgar
Youth Services Librarian
Dunlap Public Library District
302 S. First St.
Dunlap, IL 61525
309-243-5716

district’s plans for providing special education services to students with disabilities who attend private schools and home schools within the district for the 2019-2020 school year.
If you are a parent of a home-schooled student who has been, or may be identified with a disability, and you reside within the boundaries of Dunlap CUSD #323, you are urged to attend. If you have further questions pertaining to this meeting, please contact Alyssa
Hart at (309)691-3955.

post_text:
Announcement of New Board of Education

At last night's special meeting, the Board of Education seated it's new members and elected new officers. The board now consists of the following members as shown from left to right on the attached photo:

Ann Henry, Cheryl Bluth, Abby Humbles (President), Tim Wagenbach (Secretary), Mike Wisdom, Karen Disharoon (Vice-president), and Theresa Holshouser.

Congratulations to the newly elected and re-elected board members and officers!

I would like to also extend a special thank you to outgoing members Dawn Bozeman, Beth Rhee, and Bryan Zowin for their years of service on the board. We wish them all the best.

Congratulations to the newly elected and re-elected board members and officers!

I would like to also extend a special thank you to outgoing members Dawn Bozeman, Beth Rhee, and Bryan Zowin for their years of service on the board. We wish them all the best.

post_text: Dunlap High School's "Stage 323" is holding auditions for the following Von Trapp children to be in our production of "The Sound of Music" - Frederick, age 14, Kurt age 11, and Gretl, age 5. Although students auditioning for these roles do not have to be that exact age, they need to look and act like they are that age. Show dates are January 18-20, 2019. If cast in the show, students would need to be able to attend rehearsals starting right away which are scheduled for Sunday evenings and weekdays after school at the high school. Auditions will be held in the DHS Auditorium on Monday, October 29 at 4:00 PM. Students auditioning are asked to memorize a little dialogue and a song provided in advance. Please email Theatre Director Robin Hunt at rhunt@dunlapcusd.net to receive the audition materials or if you have any questions.
